text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia johnsonii, commonly known as gereera wattle or geereva wattle, is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae that is native to parts of eastern Australia.
The shrub typically grows to a height of 1.5 to 3 m (4 ft 11 in to 9 ft 10 in) and branches and producing golden flowers.
The shrub has a wide distribution through south eastern Queensland and central New South Wales.
